body:
**Describe the bug**
When I call the API with the below code using an accesstoken and try to write the resulting GHIssue objects, I get a JSON file that grews a few kilobytes every few seconds. I stopped when it reached almost 1 MB after quite some time because I think there is something very wrong. I would not expect such a large result because the Repo only has 2 issues with no comments etc.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
```
    List<GHIssue> issues =
      GitHubBuilder().withOAuthToken(accessToken).build().getRepository(fullRepoName).getIssues(GHIssueState.ALL);
    ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();
    objectMapper.getSerializerProvider().setNullKeySerializer(new DtoNullKeySerializer());
    objectMapper.writeValue(Path.of(destinationPath.toString(), "issues.json").toFile(), issues);
```

DtoNullKeySerializer:

```
package com.codingspiderfox.githubmanager.serialization;

import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonGenerator;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializerProvider;
import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ser.std.StdSerializer;
import java.io.IOException;

public class DtoNullKeySerializer extends StdSerializer<Object> {
  public DtoNullKeySerializer() {
    this(null);
  }

  public DtoNullKeySerializer(Class<Object> t) {
    super(t);
  }

  @Override
  public void serialize(Object nullKey, JsonGenerator jsonGenerator, SerializerProvider unused)
      throws IOException {
    jsonGenerator.writeFieldName("");
  }
}

```

**Expected behavior**
A full JSON representation in the resulting file with all the data the API returns about the issues (including response header fields)

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - Ubuntu 18.04
